\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Do you know why you made all these moves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes, me mother wasn't satisfied with the ho
use, it was mother as did it. She wanted somewhere better she went and she went and got the house. She was the boss. She went and got the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 In those days you could get houses easily couldn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes, you'd get houses very easily because in
 those days people - known characters, they go in a house, they wouldn't pay any rent and then there run this rent up there was another house, well there was any amount of houses vacant at that time. They used to what we called a moonlight. They'd go in t
he night and go and reside in another house. And do the same again on the landlord.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 How many rooms did you have in the house in Bridge Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 It'd - it'd three bedrooms. Well, two and a box}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6498467\charrsid3805323 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 room and - living room and kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Where would you eat and where would you cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 We - cooked in the kitchen and we ate in the living room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Can you tell me what type of cooking arrangements your mother had in those days, was it gas or a range?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 It was the old - old range. Yes. What we call the old Yorkshire range.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 The boys always followed the fathers into the mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 
In the majority of cases. They followed them into the mill because the - mill in those days was supposed to be the elite of - of the industries. Yes. Yes, in Lancashire. The new spinners.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Was your father in the mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes, my father was a mule spinner, so was his father, so was - me mother's father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Did your boys all follow you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 They all followed in. They follow}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6498467\charrsid3805323 ed in}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323  - me father made them all go into the mill. At twelve years of age. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Do you remember where your father came from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes, he came from }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6498467\charrsid3805323 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323  Stalybridge. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 And your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Same place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Did your mother work before she was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13379478 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Do you know what she did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 She worked in the mill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Did both your parents like the mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 
Yes. Yes. Yes. We all liked the mill. Yes, because - the mill in those days - the work wasn't as hard as what it is today. It wasn't as hard as it is today, no. I
n - in the spinning room you'd more people to the machine than you have now and the quality of cotton they they was using was far better than it is today. And it made it far better and far easier. And - the man - the spinner that was in charge of the spin
ning mule, he'd two or three more working with him and it meant that his job was far easier. His job was far easier, it were more in a supervisory capacity on the mules.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Was your father ever out of work - do you ever remember it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 No. No, he was never out of work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 You told me about the strike last time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 
Yes - the reason we came to live in this district a Mrs - from the information given to me by me parents was that - when my father got spinning, what we call in charge of a pair of mules
 in his young days the proprietors of the mill owned some old cottage property and they put these men in as spinners wh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6498467\charrsid3805323 en a house come vacant ay an ex}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 orbi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6498467\charrsid3805323 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 
ant rent. When they put - give me father notice to go in this house he refused to go in. And - me mother's brothers - two brothers and me grandfather worked at the mill so they came out on strike. The s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6498467\charrsid3805323 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 rike was settled, they agreed not to force them to go into the houses again but they wouldn't allow me father or me two uncles and me grandfather to work 
there. And it meant - that they it was under the Oldham district then - that they couldn't get work in Oldham. They was blacklisted by the employers in Oldham. So - at that time the Bolton Textile Mill was opening at Moses Gate in Farnworth. And - me uncl
e came to be there as a first overlooke}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6498467\charrsid3805323 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323  and me father and me grandfather followed him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 But he did at least break this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 He broke - yes, he broke - he broke it down and - one uncle went to America to become the manager of the American Thread Compa
ny in Westerly. Where I - I've had two brothers working there since - in these latter years. They went to America and I've a sister there also - working at a mill close to. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Did your mother work after she had children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Was there just yourselves lived in the house - you only had three bedrooms didn't you?;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 So you wouldn't have room for relatives or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 No, we hadn't. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Can you tell me the sleeping arrangements of your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Well - you sl
ept - the boys slept as far as you could in one room and the girls in another room. And the parents with probably - the younger children as - the family got bigger slept in the same room as the parents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Did your mother have any paid help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Was the washing done at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes. And the baking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 She did baking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Did she make jam and things like that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Or pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 No, she used to make pickles but not jam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Do you remember her making medicine or beer or wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes. Yes. Yes. She tried to make - beer and stout. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Did it work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Well - it did work but it - it wasn't the - up to the quality of the sold in public houses in those days. But it was beer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 What about medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 
Well - yes - if you had pimples the first thing that mother rushed to was brimstone and treacle. If - if you'd a cold it was goose grease.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Did you get a sweet after the brimstone and treacle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 No. No. You had - yes - but you used to do - after goose grease if - if there was any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 You had a sweet after goose grease?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes, if there was any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Did your father help your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Very little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Did he undress you or talk to you or read stories - anything at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 N
o, very - very little, very little. No. There was only father mattered in those days. The father - he was the head of the house and he had a - a clean collar and a clean shoe - his shoes cleaned to go out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 And your mother did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Well our mother or we had to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Did your father ever mend shoes or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 
He tried. Yes. Well - you see, there was very few shoes worn in those days except at Sunday. At Saturday and Sunday, otherwise it was clogs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 You had special clothes for Sunday did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes. Yes. Special clothes for Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Did your mother make or mend any clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 
Yes, she mended them - especially for the girls. She made - a lot of their clothes. She made their - their clothes and she made such as curtains and things of that description.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 And she repaired?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Were they new or secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Do you remember where you bought them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes. I remember where you bought them because in those days practically everyone used the tic shop. Practically everyone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 When you used the special tic shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 
That was so, you never knew how much there was. They used to put it in their book and - the people never took the trouble of checking up on these and they didn't know wheth
er they was being robbed or not which they were just - the majority was being. They was being robbed also at the grocers, where they got their weekly grocers, they charge what they want - wanted because it had to go on the book. And they paid every Friday
.
 And when it came holiday times when there was no holiday pay or anything of that description they couldn't pay when there was no wage and it used to take them a little bit off every week to get straight for the next holidays. They was always so much behi
n
d you see. And for the clothes - the majority of clothes they - they got through what was known in those days they call in the Scotchman. The door to door draper that went round - oh yes, he went round to door to door getting orders, see, get you anything
 
you wanted and they paid so much a week for that. It cost them a lot because - there was some - there was some acute people in those days you know. They were French - Scotchman as they call him come round they used to say, send him to our house, let him m
easure me for a suit. They used to pay their first installment but he had to whistle for the lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 He wasn't as sh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6498467\charrsid3805323 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 ewd as the Scots are supposed to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 No he wasn't - no, he wasn't as shrewd but he could afford - to - let those go because he knew he was getting out of the other people.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Was there any special time you had new clothes for do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes, Whitsuntide. Whitsuntide. Whit Friday. Yes. Whit Friday. A lot of people in those days, they run into debt - to get the children the
se clothes for Whit Friday and they never saw them again, they used to go to the pawnshop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Do you remember the pawn shops?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes. Yes. They used to go to the pawnshop and - they were left there and then they went in debt again to get some more for
 the following Whit Friday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 And they'd be in the pawnshop all the year round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 It would be a very expensive way of buying clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 It was a - it was a very expensive way for poor people because they didn't realize it in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 You felt that they weren't good at economics then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 
Well - economics as regards the working class then, in those days was a nonentity. It was a nonentity altogether. You see, schooling in those days - it was very poor. Because there was no
 - Government schools - there was all church schools. And the majority of parents all they thought about was getting their children to twelve years of age - to go work half time. And you see - you could go half time but you must have so many }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6498467\charrsid3805323 attendanc}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 es in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Did you go half time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes, I went half time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 What age did you start?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Twelve. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 You finished at twelve?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 No, I started at twelve and I finished at thirteen. I - I went twelve month half time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 What age did you start school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 I started school at - I think it was three. Yes. Yes, you had a start in what we call the babies class at three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Did you go a full day then or half a day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Well - you used to go - it wasn't a - full time, it just depended how the other children could get you there. But they - they wasn't -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 You mean your sisters or brothers took you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 They took you, yes, but you were what - what they call in the infants class. Until you was five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 And then you went full time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes. And went -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 What kind of a school was it you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 It was a - a Wesleyan school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 A church school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Was it mixed - boys and girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes, mixed boys and girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 What time did you finish when you went full time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 At school? Started at nine 'til twelve, and had an hour and half for lunch and then 'til four o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 It's pretty much the same as today?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Did you come home to your lunch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 What did you think of school - did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 
Well - I didn't like it. No. Because I didn't seem to be getting anywhere. No. I didn't feel I was getting anywhere. Because - I think you - taking me mind back as I have done and - and looking at these things, I thought it was only 
a matter of the teachers getting their time over 'til you was twelve years of age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 What did you feel about your teachers generally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Well - you see, there wasn't the qualified teachers as you have today. You didn't get the qualified teachers as y
ou have today at all. There was very few.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 And you didn't feel they gave you the attention?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 No, you didn't get the attention.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 What form of punishment did they use in those days at school - what did you get punished for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 The least - the least bit of a thing. Yes, it didn't matter what it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 How did they punish you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 They punish you - with - the cane on the hand. Yes. Always the cane on the hand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Did they punish the boys and the girls the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes. Yes. Well, girls not quite so much as the boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Do you remember any particular thing they did punish you for? Do you ever remember being punished yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes. Well for doing any sort of boy's tricks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Such as?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 I couldn't tell you what they was but I've done all the boys tricks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 And you got all the stick for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Do you remember what they emphasized as important in life at school in those days, manners or tidiness, punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes, well there was punctuality and clean clo
gs. Yes. They used to send you home if you hadn't cleaned your clogs of a morning. They used to send you home to clean them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 And punctuality was another thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Did your parents show an interest in the school in those days did they ever visit the school or see the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 
No. They never used to go to the school at all. And it was very very rare - a parent went to the school to complain over the child being punished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Because they must have thought they deserved it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 So really whatever the teachers did they go away with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 
Yes, but - the - the discipline of the children was far better in those days - than it is today, far better. I don't think the punishment that they received at the school - what I saw of th
e schools generally - did them any harm at all. You can put it on tape because - they used to threaten if you did anything wrong at all you'd have to go to the reformatory.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Do you know anybody that did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 No, I didn't. I didn't know anyone in my s
chooldays that went. But they - still the parents seemed to - hold this over you and you were afraid of it. Yes. Yes, I'd heard stories of it and you was afraid of the police. Yes, you was afraid of the police.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Why were you afraid of the police?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 
Well - you see, your parents really - made you that way in the first instance. Yes, yes, I'll bring the policeman, this that and the other you see and - you used to be afraid. When you got a bit older - the police really showed us they - was the boss over
 the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 In what way did they show this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 
Because - if you did anything they didn't like they hit you with their cape. Hit you with their cape, you see - in those days, boys - we used to play - Co}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6498467\charrsid3805323 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 perative Society and - and had their shops 
in Stoneclough and were some spare ground at side and the lads - because the shops was open late at night and there was some shops there and it - all they like come on the spare ground and we used to go playing marbles. And then all at once the police'd g
o up - Owd Cock, they call him that, the policeman, Owd Cock. The next thing he came flying round the corner with his cape and you all flew out of the way. And he used to pick all your marbles up. He used to take your marbles. Never got them back.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 How do you think he treated the people the policeman in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Well - he - he showed them in the village that he was the boss.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 They always refer to Carnworth as the village don't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes, no, this was in Lower Kearsley. Yes, down Stoneclough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 And he would show them that he was the boss?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes. Yes. Yes, he showed them that he was the boss.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 In your school did all the children come from a similar type of background as you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 No, there was - there was different - you see,
 there was co - there - it was mostly colliers and cotton workers. And the boys at twelve was put in half time into the mill up to being fourteen and then when they was fourteen the majority of them followed their parents into the pit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 So they were all similar backgrounds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 
There was all similar backgrounds, all my pals in those days that - their parents was colliers, they left the mill, they worked in the mill alongside of me and they left the mill when they became fourteen and they went to work at the mines.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Did you ever remember teachers singling some children out for different treatment to others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Can you remember what it was for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Well - it was - it was the family background and they used to be singled out and given special tuition. Yes. Special Tuition.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Because they came from better parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 
Because they came from a - what they called - thought was better homes. Where they'd a smaller family. And - they was able to - dress them better than the other people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Were there any gangs or groups in this school and were some children left out of things - do you remember this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Well - there was to a certain extent but there were very few left out, they mostly the groups was out - out of school. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Would you have stayed on longer if you'd had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 If - yes, if I'd have been allowed to take further education I'd have stayed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6498467\charrsid3805323  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Did you do any evening classes at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 No, I refused.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 For the simple - me mother tried to shove it down me - down me throu}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6498467\charrsid3805323 gh }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 at when I - -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6498467\charrsid3805323 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 
eft school to go to evening classes. Because of her two brothers that both went to - what was called Owen's College in those days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 It became Manchester University?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes.. And - they bo
th - they both got scholarships for - from there and I tell you - one finished up as manager in America and the other finished up as a manager here so - she wanted me to do it. Well when you was starting work at six o'clock in the morning you'd got to - i
t took you half an hour to get to your work. It was six o'clock when you got home of a night. I wasn't - I wasn't prepared to go to night}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6498467\charrsid3805323  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 school because none of me pals went to night}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6498467\charrsid3805323  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 school and I wasn't prepared to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Do you think you benefited from your education or do you have any regret as about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 No, I've no regrets at all. I've no regrets at all but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 You think you benefited from it though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes. I did benefit up to a - up to a point but - I've realized since I've got older th
at I - I could have gone a lot further if I'd had further education.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Of course you started part time work and school didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 How many years did you do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Twelve months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 You never had a part time job as well for spends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Did you have any jobs to help at home with as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Helping the older children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes. We all had to run errands or wa}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6498467\charrsid3805323 nd}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 s up - things of that description. If mother wanted you to do something you had to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 She was the boss?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 She was the boss.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Did you help he younger children or the younger children help the older ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes, they had to help - older ones had to help the younger ones to go to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Did you have to go to bed at a certain time in your schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 What time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes. You had to go to bed - at nine o'clock. At nine o'clock, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Who put you to bed when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Your mother. Mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 What age do you remember putting yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Why - round about six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 What room did you bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 
Bath in? You had to bath in the tin bath at front of the fire. Yes. Up to being about - see - ten years of age when there was some new houses built, along row of houses built in the village 
and in that long row of houses there was three houses with baths in. And me mother as usual was after something better, she got one of these with the bath in.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 What address was this at then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 That was in Church Road at Presaliegh. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 How many times did you put clean clothes on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes, once a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Were there any special occasions when you ate in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 No, there wasn't, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Can you tell me what time breakfast was eaten and if all the family had it together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 
No - you hadn't it together for - come to that. You see, we used to have to - mother used to get us up at morning, father worked in the mill, he had to take his breakfast to the mill. We had. We had to take his break -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Was it a cooked breakfast or sandwiches?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Oh a cooked breakfast. Yes. It was egg - egg and bacon. Something like that - every day, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Did you children have the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 No, we didn't have the same and they used to a - a can of tea. Owed to take that and the mill was six st
orey high and if - he worked in the top room you'd all those steps to walk up. Yes. And - you'd got to come back and then have your breakfast. And there was always a bit of bacon and even if it wasn't a full egg there was half egg each. Yes. Even in a big
 family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Cotton working was a good job in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes. But with a big family you see - it didn't go far with a big family. But me mother always saw that we had something to eat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Did she ever go short so that you could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes. And she went - she went into deb}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6498467\charrsid3805323 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 . She was same as them all. She shopped at the shops and paid weekly but she always saw that we had a good meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 So really your mother paid though the eyes and nose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes she did. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 This was very cruel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 What about dinners - how many times a week did you have meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 
Well - well - we always seemed to have meat in some form or another. Every day. In some form or another and that's where me - way my parents - my mother was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 She believed in good food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 She believed in - in feeding us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 This was a Lancashire tradition wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes. It was a stew or a hot-pot or something of that description, yes, every day.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 What about tea meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Well - yes, we used to - sometimes it was jam but - if there were anything at all she used to get it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Did they grow their own vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Or keep livestock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Were you allowed to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Were you allowed to leave the table when you wanted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Were you taught to use your knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 No. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Did you have your own place at table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes. You had your own place at the - and - sometimes - they weren't all in 
together, the others used to come in afterwards, used to come in what we called penny numbers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 As they started work you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Ye - no, they'd been }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13984732\charrsid3805323 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 ut playing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 They didn't all sit down together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 No. They used - they used come and - they used get down and mother s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13984732\charrsid3805323 h}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13984732\charrsid3805323 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 d give them their meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Could you leave anything on your plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Were you allowed to bring a toy or a book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 No. If we did - she'd have snatched it off us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Were you allowed to leave when you wanted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes. Yes, oh yes, we never asked, we left when we wanted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Suppose you wanted something on the table did you have to wait until it was passed or did you ask for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 We asked for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Who served the meal and who was served first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 
Well - mother served it and she weren't partial, if - we had meal when father come home well he was served first. Yes, otherwise she wasn't partial, she'd give any of us.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Did your dad get a bigger helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes, he got - he got - always got the biggest helping.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Because he was the worker?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes, he was the worker.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Where did the younger children sit before they were able to feed themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Well - mother used to
 have 'em on't knee or they used to have a high chair - high chair for those that couldn't but otherwise they sat at the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 What age would they start coming to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 As, -- well we should say about - three or four, as soon as ever they could sit on a chair.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Was your mother easy to talk to and affectionate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 You could bring your worries to her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 What about your dad, was he the strict Victorian father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Well he seemed, I told you, only father mattered - matter as long as he went out. As long as he got his pint and his bacca.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 He used to go out a great deal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 About how many nights a week would he}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13984732\charrsid3805323  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 stay home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Well - there was a lot of them in those days. Oh no. But - in thos
e days, you can put it, this down, in those days there was very little for men to do. They had to create their own, there was mostly wrestling, there were a lot of wrestling in the district. Well - there was wrestling, there was whippet racing and - there
 was pigeon flying.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Did your father take part in any of that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Me father didn't take part}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13984732\charrsid3805323  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 in any of 'em but he used to - go and watch the whippet racing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 He didn't take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 No, he didn't. No, he - he used to go and watch 
it but he didn't take part in it. But there was a lot of pigeon flying. And - whippet racing and - wrestling. And running. Yes, and it was all - all for money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Did your father go to races or did he bet on anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Well - we didn't know. He probably would bet. Yes, because there was a lot of betting. A lot of betting in those days. Betting }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13984732\charrsid3805323 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323  race}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13984732\charrsid3805323 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 house betting was illegal. Only - through the post or by telephone. But there used to be bookmaker's runners. And they used to leave their bets with the
ir wife for their wives to put on and they used to put 'em on at their work or they used to put 'em on in a pubs or anything of that description. Until the police caught them and they were summonsed. And you see a lot of those things occurred. Bets was le
ft with certain people and they never put them on. There was bets left with people, they won and they went and drew the money and kept it themselves. They didn't tip it up to the person had given it them. Then - someone got a beating up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Were you taught to behave towards your brothers and sisters in a certain way?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 
Well - we never were taught. We used to take it for granted. We used to take it for granted. Was very little trouble as brothers and sister while we was at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 You didn't fight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 You told me that if you were hit outside you had to go and hit back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes. You had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 And your mother used to give you a clip behind the ear you said?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes, if you went in and complained about someone hitting you mother used to 
- she didn't ask any questions - she used to hit you start with, you got some more and then she asked questions afterwards and then she said go out. Fight your own battles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you'd grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Did they teach you that certain things were important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 
Well - no, they didn't, they just let us go our way like that. Just let us go our - our way, they never taught us anything, we went to Sunday school. Oh yes, we went to Sunda
y school. And - then we went to Sunday school, there was nothing else after. There was practically no youth clubs. There was nothing for you to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 So what did you do on Sunday after Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Well - you - you used to make up games of your own and when you got older you used to out walk in the mill street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 They used to call it the monkey run?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes, it was. There was a monkey run in Farnworth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 There was in every town wasn't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 There was nothing else after they'd been 
to church in the evening. Went on the monkey run and those that thought they were a bit better than the other walked on one side of the road, and the others walked on the other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 You went to Church of England did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Were there no activities at the church that you went to - do you remember any of the social activities as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 
The only social activities there was, there was school - a school concert got up every so often. There was sometimes there was a wagonette trip to -
 some - we went to Worlsey from here - we thought it was an outing. There was a - what we called a magic lantern show at the school. And then - the Racobites came. The - the - the temperance people came - the Racobites. And asked you to sign to be teetota
l.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Did you do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes, you did it. But you used to - it was only a matter of form because you was only children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Can you tell me the activities of the temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 No Racobite clubs.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 But do you remember if the church temperance club had any activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 No, no, they had none.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 It was just a matter of getting you to sign the pledge?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes. These Racobits, what they call Racobites, used to come and have what they call this magic lantern show. There were no what - li
ving pictures then and they used to show you people what drink beer and things of that description.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 What happened when you didn't drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Did you belong to any other club associated with the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes. I did one - the Church Lad
s Brigade. Yes. When I - when I became older. I joined the Church Lads Brigade and - they had certain activities. They used to have a clubroom of their own, they used to have football team and things of that. They used to go to camp.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Did you go to camp?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Yes, and that was the first time I really stayed at the seaside and it was at Scarborough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Did you ever go away for holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10167806 FH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 No, we never went away for a holiday for the simple reason the family was too big. The only time we went was -
 in those days was fishing club at every public house. There was a fishing club at every public house. Yes. And they used to go fishing towards Lancaster and those places and you was on Whit Saturday and they - the special train used to be run for the fis
hermen and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16685 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14758297\charrsid3805323 Did you go fishing too?
